    • Element Detail

      • fieldTitle

        public abstract java.lang.String fieldTitle
        field title -- a capitalized, preferrably unabbreviated name for the field.

        fieldTitle must match the label name used in activity form. Usually it coincides with fmName.

        example: "Sectors"; "AMP Internal ID"

      • label

        public abstract java.lang.String label
        Field label that will be used in UI. If not specified defaults to fieldTitle().
        Default:
        "_FIELD_TITLE_"

      • fmPath

        public abstract java.lang.String fmPath
         Path in the Feature Manager, corresponding to enabling / disabling said field in AF
 Usage examples:
 fmPath = "/Activity Form/Organization/Donor Organization"  
 fmPath = FMVisibility.ANY_FM + "/Activity Form/Organizations/Donor Organization
                                |/Activity Form/Funding/Search Funding Organizations/Search Organizations"
 fmPath = FMVisibility.PARENT_FM + "/sectorPercentage"
        Default:
        ""

      • commonPV

        public abstract java.lang.String commonPV
        Path to the common possible values that will be checked for values to avoid rebuilding the same list of options for fields that depend on the same possible values like organization lists. Note: initial usage in activity import validation. Later can use for export and values EP in AMP-25943
        Returns:
        the alias for common possible values
        Default:
        ""

      • multipleValues

        public abstract boolean multipleValues
        Whether the collection field in AF supports several values. It will be used just for collection fields (like: one activity might have several sectors assigned, or only one)

        multipleValues not supported if pickIdOnly is true and collection is discriminated. See AMP-23362.

        Default:
        true

      • importable

        public abstract boolean importable
        whether this field is to be imported on the target system example: ID fields are usually not imported, since are assigned by the importing DB automatically
        Default:
        false

      • readOnlyFmPath

        public abstract java.lang.String readOnlyFmPath
        The field is read only or not based on fm path. If readOnlyFmPath is visible, read only is true
        Default:
        ""

      • pickIdOnly

        public abstract boolean pickIdOnly
        Used during serialization to replace an object with id. The object must implement Identifiable.

        Example: 

        {@code
 class Example {
        Default:
        false

      • type

        public abstract java.lang.Class<?> type
        Default:
        org.digijava.module.aim.annotations.interchange.Interchangeable.DefaultType.class

      • dependencies

        public abstract java.lang.String[] dependencies

        Mark field whose value depends on some external condition. For example implementation location depends on implementation level. Or organization group used in pledge must match the group of the organization used in donor funding.

        To make a field required under certain conditions see requiredDependencies().

        Returns:
        list of dependencies
        Default:
        {}

      • requiredDependencies

        public abstract java.lang.String[] requiredDependencies
        Mark field as required only under some conditions. For example field becomes visible as in case of on budget fields. Or fields were visible but not required as in case of type of assistance and financing instrument.
        Returns:
        list of required dependencies
        Default:
        {}

      • dependencyRequiredFMPath

        public abstract java.lang.String dependencyRequiredFMPath
        FM entry to control dependency required validator.
        Default:
        ""

      • dependencyRequired

        public abstract ActivityEPConstants.RequiredValidation dependencyRequired
        Whether the field is always required, required for non-draft saves, or not required. Applies only for fields with dependencies.
        Default:
        org.digijava.kernel.ampapi.endpoints.activity.ActivityEPConstants.RequiredValidation.NONE

      • discriminatorOption

        public abstract java.lang.String discriminatorOption

        Filter objects by specified discriminator value. Must be specified in InterchangeableDiscriminator.settings().

        When annotating AmpCategoryValue, this value must be specified to allow listing possible values for a category class. Can be used inside InterchangeableDiscriminator.settings() or standalone.

        Category in discriminated field example: 

         @InterchangeableDiscriminator(discriminatorField="categories",
   settings = {
     @Interchangeable(fieldTitle = "Activity Status", discriminatorOption = "act_status", pickIdOnly=true),
     @Interchangeable(fieldTitle = "Type of Cooperation", discriminatorOption = "coop_type", pickIdOnly=true)
 })
 protected Set<AmpCategoryValue> categories;

        Standalone category example: 

         @Interchangeable(fieldTitle = "Adjustment Type", discriminatorOption = "adj_type", pickIdOnly = true)
 private AmpCategoryValue adjustmentType;
        Default:
        ""

      • validators

        public abstract Validators validators
        Default:

      • interValidators

        public abstract InterchangeableValidator[] interValidators
        List of constraint validators that apply to the current field.
        Default:
        {}

      • uniqueConstraint

        public abstract boolean uniqueConstraint
        Default:
        false

      • percentageConstraint

        public abstract boolean percentageConstraint
        Used to mark percentage field for an object in collection for which all percentages must sum to 100.

        Not used for validation in the backend buy might be useful for API clients in future to determine if this constraint is enabled or not (via FM rules).

        Default:
        false
